Jacque Vaughn was hired as coach of
the  Orlando Magic  as the team deals with disgruntled All-Star
center  Dwight Howard .  The National Basketball Association club announced the
addition of Vaughn in a news release. He succeeds Stan Van
Gundy, who was fired in May.  Vaughn, 37, was an assistant coach with the San Antonio
Spurs the last two seasons. He was a guard on the Spursâ€™ NBA
championship team in 2007.  Howard has a year to go on his contract and has told the
Magic he wants to be traded, He informed General Manager Rob
Hennigan this week that he would leave the Magic as a free agent
after the 2012-13 season, ESPN reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
